// ch01 §1.3: "an attribute-specifier-seq written immediately after a
// function's parameter list ... attaches to the function's *type*
// ([dcl.fct]), not to the function itself and not to its body, and so
// has no effect at all" -- this describes it as legal, if semantically
// inert, grammar (real C++ [dcl.fct] already gives a function's type
// its own optional attribute-specifier-seq in this position). As
// this position is legal but semantically inert: it appertains to the
// function type rather than making the function body unsafe.
int harmless() [[scpp::unsafe]] {
    return 5;
}

int main() {
    return harmless();
}
